# GitPM — Cursor Rules

## Project Context
GitPM is a portfolio platform for product managers who build with AI coding tools.
Phase 1: profile + project consolidation + multi-platform verification (GitHub, Vercel, Lovable).
Read ARCHITECTURE.md for full technical context before making changes.
Read BUILD_TICKETS.md for the sequenced development plan.

## Tech Stack (do not deviate)
- Next.js 14 with App Router (NOT Pages Router)
- TypeScript in strict mode — no `any` types, no `@ts-ignore`
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui for all UI components
- Supabase for database, auth, and file storage
- Vercel for hosting and serverless functions

## Code Style & Conventions

### TypeScript
- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions and intersections
- All function parameters and return types must be explicitly typed
- Use Zod for runtime validation on all API route inputs
- Export types from `types/` directory, never define inline in components
- Prefer `const` over `let`. Never use `var`
- Use early returns to reduce nesting

### React & Next.js
- Server components by default. Only use `"use client"` when the component needs:
  - useState, useEffect, or other hooks
  - Event handlers (onClick, onChange, onSubmit)
  - Browser APIs
- Never use `"use client"` on page.tsx files unless absolutely necessary — fetch data in server components and pass to client children
- Use Next.js App Router conventions: `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`
- Use `next/image` for all images with explicit width/height
- Use `next/link` for all internal navigation
- Colocate components with their routes when they're only used there

### Supabase
- ALL Supabase queries go through helpers in `lib/supabase/`
  - `lib/supabase/client.ts` — browser client (client components)
  - `lib/supabase/server.ts` — server client (server components, API routes)
  - `lib/supabase/admin.ts` — service role client (public reads, bypassing RLS)
- Never instantiate Supabase client directly in components or API routes
- Always use generated types from `types/database.ts` for query results
- Write all schema changes as migrations in `supabase/migrations/`
- RLS must be enabled on every table. No exceptions

### API Routes
- All API routes in `app/api/` directory
- Use proper HTTP methods: GET for reads, POST for creates, PATCH for updates, DELETE for deletes
- Always validate request body with Zod before processing
- Return typed JSON responses with consistent shape:
  ```ts
  // Success
  { data: T }
  // Error
  { error: string, code: string }
  ```
- Always check auth session at the top of protected routes
- Handle errors with try/catch and return appropriate status codes

### Styling
- Use Tailwind utility classes. No custom CSS files unless absolutely necessary
- Follow the design system in ARCHITECTURE.md:
  - Primary: #0D1B2A (deep navy)
  - Teal: #0A7558 (verification, success)
  - Purple: #6C5CE7 (interactive elements)
  - Dark surface: #1B2838
  - Neutral surface: #F0F2F0
  - Border: #C8CCC8 at 0.5px
- Add these as Tailwind custom colors in `tailwind.config.ts`
- Use shadcn/ui components as the base. Customize with Tailwind, don't override with raw CSS
- Design direction: dark-tilting, minimal chrome, trust-forward (Linear/Vercel aesthetic)

### File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (`ProjectCard.tsx`)
- Utilities/helpers: camelCase (`github.ts`, `thumbnails.ts`)
- Types: camelCase files, PascalCase exports (`types/project.ts` → `export interface Project`)
- API routes: `route.ts` (Next.js convention)
- Migrations: sequential numbered prefix (`001_users.sql`)

### OAuth & Security
- GitHub OAuth token comes from Supabase Auth (stored automatically)
- Vercel OAuth tokens stored in `connected_accounts` table, encrypted
- Never expose OAuth tokens to the client. All external API calls happen server-side
- Never log tokens or include them in error messages
- Use environment variables for all secrets. Reference `.env.local.example`

### Error Handling
- Wrap all async operations in try/catch
- Use toast notifications (sonner via shadcn) for user-facing errors
- Log errors server-side with context (not just the error message)
- Never show raw error messages to users
- Provide loading states and skeletons for all async UI

### Git Conventions
- Commit messages: `type: description` (e.g., `feat: add project creation form`, `fix: RLS policy for public reads`)
- Types: feat, fix, refactor, style, docs, test, chore
- One logical change per commit

## Things to NEVER Do
- Never use Pages Router patterns (getServerSideProps, getStaticProps)
- Never use `any` type
- Never query Supabase directly in components (use lib/supabase helpers)
- Never store secrets in code or commit .env files
- Never disable RLS policies, even temporarily
- Never use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` unless sanitizing with DOMPurify
- Never use inline styles. Use Tailwind classes
- Never install packages without checking if shadcn/ui already provides the functionality
- Never create API routes that don't validate input with Zod

## When Unsure
- Check ARCHITECTURE.md for system-level decisions
- Check BUILD_TICKETS.md for what should/shouldn't be in scope
- Prefer simplicity over cleverness
- Ask before adding new dependencies
- If a feature is listed under "What Phase 1 Does NOT Include" in ARCHITECTURE.md, do not build it
